captions.text:
-In this hair we're going to do
twists into a side pony tail.

And you can see her
hair isn't very long,

so it doesn't have to be super
long-haired to do this one.

Hers is just barely
below her shoulders.

And I've parted the
hair on her left, which

is where her natural
part line falls,

but you can part
it on either side.
And I've let it down.

And I just take a comb
and comb so it's smooth,

and there's not any
bumps or odd place hairs.

Then I start on this side that
has the least amount of hair.
Just pick up a little section.

And we're just doing
twists, so you just

need to divide it
into two pieces.

And then you're just
going to twist them.

And just take one
over the other,

and then pick up
hair on the bottom.
And add it in and twist.

Pick up some more
hair and twist.

Just keep twisting
and adding hair.

Just make sure that you
get those pieces smooth
as they are laying down.
Keep twisting.

This is why it was important
that you have the hair smooth

before because then it
just lays smooth here.

If there was a bump, then
you'd get a little bubble
in the hair.

Just keep twisting,
picking up hair.
Can you turn your head now?

OK, now I'm going to
do a side little bun
on the right side of her head.

So I'm going to keep
twisting, turn just a little

more, until this one's actually
a little farther than center
on the back of her head.
Do one more.

And then I'm going to have
her reach back and hold.

Can you reach back
and hold this?
Other hand, honey.
Hold it down just a little more.
There you go.

OK, while she's
holding that, I'm
going to start on this side.
I'm going to switch sides.

So again, tip your head
back just a little for me.

Start with a small section
and divide it in half.
Twist.

And just begin picking up
the hair and twisting it in.

And of course, this
side won't take

as long because you don't have
nearly as much hair since you
went off center.
Keep twisting.

So you've picked
up all of the hair.

And then when your twists are
done-- thank you, got it--

and they just bring the
hands together, kind of

over on the right
side of her head,

you can see it's
right behind her ear.

Take an elastic, and--
that will go in-- secure
the hair like a ponytail.

But on the last
one, I'm just going

to not bring it quite
through all the way

because I'm just going to do
a little fluff at the end.

And then just to
secure that, I'm

going to take a
smaller rubber band

and just kind of
go over that again,

just to have a little
extra security on that.

And her hair is
short enough, she'll

have a few pieces that
pop out over the day,
but I don't really care.

Tuck them in if you're
worried about them.

And then you can rat the ends if
you want to add a little fluff.

And then just add some
hairspray, and you're done.
